The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, July 17, 2004 				 Lights out, problems in
																								Domestic problems prevail in every household. Day after day a woman is abused, physically and mentally, but she always remains the silent sufferer, never raising her voice in protest. She is a mute victim of the psychological and emotional trauma that she constantly lives with. But our hypocritical society refuses to acknowledge the moral offence being perpetrated against the woman. No one even searches for a solution. Renowned writer and cartoonist Manjula Padmanabhans play Lights Out, directed by Jayant Kripalani, deals with such problems of domesticity from a womans point of view. As the play unfolds, one is bound to realise that in every corner of society a woman, in her diverse roles of wife, mother or daughter, suffers such domestic abuse. Kripalani, the veteran director and actor, handles this sensitive issue with great subtlety.																								Event: Lights Out  a play by Manjula Padmanabhan																								When: Today and tomorrow at 7 pm																								Where: G.D. Birla Sabhagar
